# =============================================================================
# Cortex API request catalog
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exercise the running platform from your IDE (VS Code "REST Client", JetBrains
# HTTP Client, etc.). Start the sample host first:
#   dotnet run --project samples/Cortex.Sample.AppHost      (Aspire: API on :8080)
#   # or: dotnet run --project samples/Cortex.Sample.Host
#
# Auth: in Development the API accepts dev-auth headers (X-Dev-*) that stand in
# for a real OIDC token. Change {{subject}}/{{roles}}/{{tenant}} below to act as
# a different user, role, or tenant. In production these come from Entra External
# ID and the headers are ignored.
#
# Placeholders like {{conversationId}} / {{userId}} are set to a sample GUID —
# replace them with real ids returned by the list endpoints above them.
# =============================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@subject = dev-user
@name = Dev User
@tenant = dev
@roles = system_admin

# GUID placeholders — copy real ids from the list responses.
@conversationId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@userId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@tenantId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# ── Health (anonymous) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Liveness (never calls the LLM)
GET {{baseUrl}}/alive

### Readiness / health checks
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

# ── Platform: identity + navigation ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Who am I — user, tenant, effective permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/me
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Name: {{name}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Modules + tabs the caller can see (drives the dashboard navigation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/modules
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Deployment facts (chat enabled? demo/mock mode?)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/platform/info
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

# ── Chat: a streamed agent turn ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### AG-UI turn (SSE). The Mock provider drives a real, audited tool call.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/agui/finance
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{
  "messages": [{ "role": "user", "content": "Summarize my spending using a tool." }]
}

### REST stream turn (HTTP SSE alternative to the SignalR hub)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/stream
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{
  "moduleId": "finance",
  "message": "Am I over budget on anything?"
}

# ── Chat: conversation history (own conversations) ───────────────────────────

### List my conversations for a module (newest first)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/conversations?moduleId=finance
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### A conversation's message history (owner-scoped)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/conversations/{{conversationId}}/messages
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Rename a conversation
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/conversations/{{conversationId}}/title
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "title": "Quarterly review" }

### Delete a conversation (messages cascade)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/conversations/{{conversationId}}
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

# ── Chat: human-in-the-loop approvals ────────────────────────────────────────

### Pending approvals (side-effecting tool calls blocked awaiting a human)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/approvals
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Approve a blocked call (re-executes the exact recorded call). {{approvalId}} from the list above.
# @approvalId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/approvals/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/approve
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

# ── Admin: security map + roles (platform.roles.manage) ──────────────────────

### The complete permission map: platform perms + every module tool
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/security/catalog
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Roles and the permissions each grants (built-in + custom, with editable/builtIn flags)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/roles
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Create a custom role
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/roles
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "role": "auditor", "permissions": ["platform.audit.view"] }

### Reconfigure what a role grants (replace semantics; system_admin is rejected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/roles/user/permissions
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "permissions": ["chat.use", "chat.conversations.view", "chat.approvals.manage"] }

### Delete a custom role (built-ins are rejected)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/roles/auditor
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

# ── Admin: users (platform.users.manage / roles) ─────────────────────────────

### Users in the tenant, with roles, grants, active state, external subject
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Assign a role to a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}/roles
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "role": "auditor" }

### Grant a fine-grained permission to a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}/permissions
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "permission": "tools.finance.summarize_spending" }

### Activate / deactivate a user (deactivated ⇒ denied every request; can't deactivate yourself)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}/active
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "isActive": false }

# ── Admin: per-tenant module management (platform.modules.manage) ────────────

### Installed modules + enabled state for this tenant
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/modules
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Enable / disable a module for this tenant (disabled ⇒ hidden + uninvocable)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/modules/nutrition
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "enabled": false }

# ── Admin: tenants (platform.tenants.manage; cross-tenant, operator-only) ────

### All tenants in the deployment
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tenants
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Activate / deactivate a tenant (tenant-wide kill switch; can't deactivate your own)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}/active
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "isActive": false }

# ── Admin: per-tenant AI settings (platform.ai.manage) ───────────────────────

### This tenant's AI overrides + the deployment defaults
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/ai-settings
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Override the tenant's system prompt / conversation token budget (null fields = use default)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/ai-settings
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "systemPrompt": "You are a terse assistant.", "maxConversationTokens": 50000 }

# ── Admin: audit + usage (platform.audit.view) ──────────────────────────────

### Recent agent tool-call audit entries
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/audit/tool-calls?take=50
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Recent identity / authorization events (sign-ins, grants, role & tenant changes)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/audit/auth-events?take=50
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Token usage report (totals, by module, by day)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/usage?days=30
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

# ── Sample module endpoints ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Finance — the tenant's ledger
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/finance/transactions
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Nutrition — food catalog
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/nutrition/foods?query=chicken
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

### Nutrition — log a meal to the diary (macros computed server-side)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/nutrition/diary
Content-Type: application/json
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

{ "foodName": "Chicken breast", "grams": 200 }

### Legal — clause library
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/legal/clauses
X-Dev-Subject: {{subject}}
X-Dev-Tenant: {{tenant}}
X-Dev-Roles: {{roles}}

# ── Channels: WhatsApp (off by default — Channels:WhatsApp:Enabled=true) ────
# The webhook is what Meta calls; it is anonymous but HMAC-authenticated.
# POST bodies must carry X-Hub-Signature-256 = "sha256=" + HMACSHA256(rawBody,
# AppSecret) — compute one in PowerShell:
#   $b='<body>'; $k='<AppSecret>'
#   'sha256=' + (([System.Security.Cryptography.HMACSHA256]::new([Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($k))).ComputeHash([Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($b)) | ForEach-Object ToString x2) -join ''
# The E2E suite covers this end to end without Meta: WhatsAppChannelTests.

### Meta webhook verification handshake (echoes hub.challenge when the token matches)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/channels/whatsapp/webhook?hub.mode=subscribe&hub.verify_token=<VerifyToken>&hub.challenge=12345

### Inbound message delivery (replace the signature — see comment above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/channels/whatsapp/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
X-Hub-Signature-256: sha256=<hmac-of-raw-body>

{"object":"whatsapp_business_account","entry":[{"id":"waba-1","changes":[{"field":"messages","value":{"messaging_product":"whatsapp","contacts":[{"wa_id":"5215550100","profile":{"name":"Dev"}}],"messages":[{"id":"wamid.local-1","from":"5215550100","type":"text","text":{"body":"How much did I spend on groceries?"}}]}}]}]}
